article.headline: San Diego 89, Occidental 53
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Brandon Gay scored a game-high 26 points to lead San Diego to an 89-53 win over Occidental Monday night. San Diego (2-1) scored the first 12 points of the game, then used a 14-0 run to jump out to a 35-12 lead at the 5:47 mark of the first half. The Toreros had 13 assists and made eight lay-ups as they took a 46-20 halftime lead. Division III Occidental (2-1), missed its first five shots and committed three turnovers on its first eight possessions. The Tigers hit just 38 percent of their field goals in the game (19 of 50). Gay was 9-for-14 from the floor, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range, and had seven rebounds. Brett Melton made 4 of 10 3-pointers and finished with 14 points. Bryce Vounang scored 11 points and had nine rebounds. Joe Sasich led Occidental with 15 points and Dylan Marvin and Zach Phillips scored 11 points each. The Tigers finished with 23 turnovers and were out-rebounded 41-26. San Diego's two victories have come against non-Division I schools, including Saturday's 39-point win over UC San Diego, a Division II school.
